:"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"body":"This should do it.  Adds the comparator as 'compareWith' as well as revert type to mean Super or Standard, and converts 'flushperiod' to 'flushPeriod' for consistency.\r\n\r\nOutput on default storage-conf:\r\n\r\n$ ./Cassandra-remote -h 127.0.0.1:9160 describeTable \"Table1\"\r\n{ 'Standard1': { 'compareWith': 'org.apache.cassandra.db.marshal.UTF8Type',\r\n                 'desc': 'Table1.Standard1(ROW_KEY, COLUMN_MAP(COLUMN_KEY, COLUMN_VALUE, COLUMN_TIMESTAMP))',\r\n                 'flushPeriod': '60',\r\n                 'type': 'Standard'},\r\n  'Standard2': { 'compareWith': 'org.apache.cassandra.db.marshal.UTF8Type',\r\n                 'desc': 'Table1.Standard2(ROW_KEY, COLUMN_MAP(COLUMN_KEY, COLUMN_VALUE, COLUMN_TIMESTAMP))',\r\n                 'flushPeriod': '0',\r\n                 'type': 'Standard'},\r\n  'StandardByUUID1': { 'compareWith': 'org.apache.cassandra.db.marshal.UUIDType',\r\n                       'desc': 'Table1.StandardByUUID1(ROW_KEY, COLUMN_MAP(COLUMN_KEY, COLUMN_VALUE, COLUMN_TIMESTAMP))',\r\n                       'flushPeriod': '0',\r\n                       'type': 'Standard'},\r\n  'Super1': { 'compareWith': 'org.apache.cassandra.db.marshal.UTF8Type',\r\n              'desc': 'Table1.Super1(ROW_KEY, SUPER_COLUMN_MAP(SUPER_COLUMN_KEY, COLUMN_MAP(COLUMN_KEY, COLUMN_VALUE, COLUMN_TIMESTAMP)))',\r\n              'flushPeriod': '0',\r\n              'type': 'Super'}}\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"created":"2009-07-23T19:21:11.232+0000","updated":"2009-07-23T19:21:11.232+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12431286/comment/12734748","id":"12734748","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"body":"Incorporates Evan's suggestion to mirror storage-conf naming instead of arbitrary names.  Follows CamelCase standard set there.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=euphoria","name":"euphoria","emailAddress":"michael dot greene at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Michael Greene","active":true},"created":"2009-07-23T19:35:45.955+0000","updated":"2009-07-23T19:35:45.955+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12431286/comment/1273476